<p>
<seg id=1> Ladies and gentlemen, let's take a look at the situation in China. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=2> The Chinese government detained a few dissidents a few days ago in order to prevent the meeting of some Chinese Democratic Party members in Zhejiang and Shanghai. </seg>
<seg id=3> Please listen to the report in Chinese from VOA, spoken by Qing Yue. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> According to the news from the Chinese Human Rights Democratic Movement Information Center, whose center is in Hong Kong, Hang Zhou police took Zhu Zhengming and Mao Qingxiang, two members of the Chinese Democratic Party away, from their homes respectively. </seg>
<seg id=5> So far, nothing has been heard of the two men. </seg>
<seg id=6> Before that, the police had arrested other four core members of the democratic movement who are closely related with the Chinese Democratic Party--they are Yao Zhenxian, Li Guotao, Wu Yilong and Wang Rongqing. </seg>
<seg id=7> According to the Information Center of Chinese Human Rights and Democratic Movement, about twenty members of the Chinese Democratic Party of the Zhejiang and Shanghai branches originally planned to meet at a restaurant in Hangzhou City on Friday afternoon to hold their first conference. </seg>
<seg id=8> The police was directed against this meeting and took action of arrest. </seg>
<seg id=9> In addition, the police in various parts of Zhejiang Province also gave warning to the active members of the democratic movement that they should not go out of their home or they would be arrested. </seg>
<seg id=10> The Chinese government regards the opposition party, the Chinese Democratic Party, as an illegal organization, and has detained and interrogated tens of active members and supporters of this organization. </seg>
<seg id=11> However, they were quickly released in most cases. </seg>
<seg id=12> US Associated Press, Reuters and Agence France-Press reported respectively the lastest news released by the Information Center of Chinese Human Rights and Democratic Movement. </seg>
</p>
